docs.abstract: A journalist who loved to needle the Manhattan elite enrages the president with his insider account of the year he spent reporting from the West Wing.
docs.snippet: A journalist who loved to needle the Manhattan elite enrages the president with his insider account of the year he spent reporting from the West Wing.
docs.lead_paragraph: Michael Wolff has, for years, been a prime piranha in the Manhattan media pond, using his caustic columns to tear into his lunchmates at Michael’s, the Midtown mogul canteen, and cutting a memorable figure at star-speckled dinner parties, clad in Charvet ties and shirts by the London haberdashery Browns.

headline.main: Michael Wolff, From Local Media Scourge to National Newsmaker
headline.print_headline: From a New York News Media Scourge to a Newsmaker on a National Scale

docs.abstract: The piece, written by John Moody and published on FoxNews.com, sarcastically suggested that the motto for the U.S. Olympic Committee should be “Darker, Gayer, Different.”
docs.snippet: The piece, written by John Moody and published on FoxNews.com, sarcastically suggested that the motto for the U.S. Olympic Committee should be “Darker, Gayer, Different.”
docs.lead_paragraph: Fox News on Friday removed an incendiary op-ed article by one of its top executives, after the piece drew criticism for mocking American Olympic officials who had emphasized the diversity of this year’s team of athletes. The column suggested, sarcastically, that the United States Olympic Committee adopt a new motto: “Darker, Gayer, Different.”

headline.main: Fox News Column Mocking Olympic Team Diversity Draws Outrage
headline.print_headline: Fox News  Scraps Article By Executive After Uproar

docs.abstract: At a cabinet meeting, the return of the president as press critic, after his legal maneuvers against BuzzFeed and the publisher of Michael Wolff’s book.
docs.snippet: At a cabinet meeting, the return of the president as press critic, after his legal maneuvers against BuzzFeed and the publisher of Michael Wolff’s book.
docs.lead_paragraph: President Trump on Wednesday repeated a pledge to make it easier for people to sue news organizations and publishers for defamation, denouncing the country’s libel laws as a “sham” a day after his personal lawyer filed a lawsuit against a major media outlet, BuzzFeed News.

headline.main: Trump Renews Pledge to ‘Take a Strong Look’ at Libel Laws
headline.print_headline: Trump Again Vows Review Of ‘Sham’ U.S. Libel Laws

docs.abstract: The lawsuit accuses Fox News of “extreme and outrageous” conduct and claims that a reporter and network contributor intentionally fabricated the story.
docs.snippet: The lawsuit accuses Fox News of “extreme and outrageous” conduct and claims that a reporter and network contributor intentionally fabricated the story.
docs.lead_paragraph: The parents of Seth Rich, the young Democratic aide whose unsolved murder became grist for right-wing conspiracy theories about the 2016 presidential race, filed a lawsuit on Tuesday against Fox News, claiming that the network’s coverage helped fuel damaging rumors about their son.

headline.main: Family of Seth Rich Sues Fox News Over Retracted Article
headline.print_headline: Slain Aide’s Family Sues Fox News

docs.lead_paragraph: The CBS News program “60 Minutes” was moving forward with plans to show an interview it conducted last week with the pornographic film actress who says she had an affair with Donald J. Trump as her lawyer and a lawyer for the president traded public jabs through the weekend over her right to speak.

headline.main: As ‘60 Minutes’ Prepares Stormy Daniels Interview, Lawyers Wrangle
headline.print_headline: Lawyers Wrangle as ‘60 Minutes’ Prepares to Air Porn Star Interview

docs.abstract: President Trump made good on his promise to honor the media’s “most corrupt & biased,” delivering his awards in a blog post.
docs.snippet: President Trump made good on his promise to honor the media’s “most corrupt & biased,” delivering his awards in a blog post.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump — who gleefully questioned President Barack Obama’s birthplace for years without evidence, long insisted on the guilt of the Central Park Five despite exonerating proof and claimed that millions of illegal ballots cost him the popular vote in 2016 — wanted to have a word with the American public about accuracy in reporting.

headline.main: Trump Hands Out ‘Fake News Awards,’ Sans the Red Carpet
headline.print_headline: May We Have the ‘Fake’ Envelope, Please?

byline.original: By Matt Flegenheimer and Michael M. Grynbaum

docs.abstract: The appointment of Ms. Scott by the Murdoch family elevated an executive closely tied with the Roger Ailes regime that became mired in a sexual harassment scandal.
docs.snippet: The appointment of Ms. Scott by the Murdoch family elevated an executive closely tied with the Roger Ailes regime that became mired in a sexual harassment scandal.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Murdochs named Suzanne Scott the new chief executive of Fox News on Thursday, making her the first woman to lead the cable news network even as her appointment signaled the elevation of an executive closely tied with the old regime that was largely ousted in the wake of a sexual harassment scandal.

headline.main: Suzanne Scott Named First Female Chief Executive of Fox News
headline.print_headline: Murdochs Elevate First Woman, An Ailes Ally, To Lead Fox News
